news.title: DLF phase 1-3 residents await infra work & takeover by Gurugram civic body
news.para: MCG officials said the deadline was over on December 31 last year, but the developer has not yet started work on internal roads. The civic body will now submit a report to the state government on the status of the takeover of the three private colonies.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body starts digitising property tax files
news.para: Out of around 1.20 lakh files of both residential and commercial properties, over 15,000 are already digitised. Not only documents, details of taxes paid and arrears, will be maintained digitally by the tax branch of the civic body.

news.title: Interest subsidy of Rs 41,415 crore disbursed so far under PMAY-Urban: Government
news.para: Union Housing and Urban Affairs Minister Hardeep Singh Puri said subsidy of Rs 5,320 crore has been disbursed so far under the Credit Linked Subsidy Scheme (CLSS) in the current financial year.

news.title: DDA extends last date to apply for special housing scheme
news.para: The new special housing scheme offers a little over 18,000 flats, with all units being drawn from its old inventory. The last date of the scheme was February 7, 2022, when it was announced.

news.title: GNIDA to impose Rs 10 lakh fine on unauthorised use of authority logo
news.para: Any companies or builders found using the GNIDA logo without permission will be charged a fine of Rs 10 lakh followed by cancellation lease deed.

news.title: Livspace turns unicorn with $180 million KKR-led funding
news.para: The home renovation platform is the 86th "unicorn" from India, according to Venture Intelligence Unicorn Tracker, in a period of record funding in Indian start-ups that saw 43 firms join the club last year alone.

news.title: Aurum PropTech to acquire 53% stake in Grexter Housing Solutions for Rs 27 crore
news.para: Grexter Living will be utilising this growth capital to scale up its business in co-living space. It is aiming to strengthen product offering by improving its technology platform and focusing on community-led engagement in its co-living spaces.

news.title: Gera Developments forays into US property market with projects in San Francisco
news.para: Gera Developments has set up its wholly owned US subsidiary, Outdo Inc. to invest in these project special purpose vehicles. Outdo Inc. owns a 50% stake in the first two projects, while the balance is with its partner, a US-based developer.

news.title: Arttech acquires 7.3-acre land for Rs 70 crore in Faridabad
news.para: “Faridabad is taking giant leaps forward in terms of development with an infrastructure boost and economic growth,” said Saurabh Shatdal, managing director-capital markets, Cushman & Wakefield India, which facilitated the deal.

news.title: Commence demolition of Supertech's twin tower in Noida within two weeks: SC
news.para: A bench comprising Justices D Y Chandrachud and Surya Kant also directed the Noida CEO to convene a meeting within 72 hours in which all the agencies concerned shall be present.

news.title: Development projects to ride on Kovalam-Vizhinjam master plan
news.para: The council has approved the formation of a special committee regarding height, coverage and other aspects of development projects in all the zones within the scheme area.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Panel backs greens on Panje wetland, junks Cidco's claim
news.para: During the latest meeting held by the HC-appointed wetland panel, one of its members, D Stalin, stood strong on his stand that Panje is a wetland since intertidal waters are still seen here and continue to attract hundreds of wetland birds, like the flamingos.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body set aside 31 plots for infrastructure projects
news.para: The plots will be utilized for parks, common facilities built by the civic body and even government agencies that provide civic services.

news.title: Jaipur civic body seals three commercial buildings for lack of fire NOC
news.para: The action was taken after issuing the notices to the violators. The corporation sealed OK tower on Ajmer Road, Gulabi Nagar restaurant near Collectrate circle and Vishal Mega Mart.

news.title: Ludhiana: Audit & accounts department orders illegal buildings' checking
news.para: Around five years ago, the local bodies department additional chief secretary had ordered action against illegal buildings, but the directions were hardly implemented, causing loss of Rs 100 crore to the MC and the Punjab government.
